                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d167">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/11034: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-02T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 2, 1930—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>260. Tokyo’s 128, August 1, 4 p.m. Japanese Embassy has informed Department of
                    demand that National Government take effective measures, but not of offer of
                    Japanese Government to initiate common action with National Government and not
                    of ordering of additional Japanese forces to Hankow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Carr</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
